). Legs about half length of body. Leg segments’ setal formulae: coxae 2-1-2-1; trochanters 1-1-1-1; femora 3-3-2-2, genua 3-0-0-0; tibiae 5+1’ρ–5+1’ρ–5+1’ρ–5+1’ρ; tarsi 11+1ω– 9+1ω–7+1ω–7+1ω. Specialized setae ’ρ on tibia I one and half times longer than on tibia II and two times of tibiae III-IV. Solenidion ω on tarsus I longer than on tarsi II-IV.
